t%3BA%20lot%20of%20students%20who%20take%20philosophy%20classes%2C%20especially%20if%20they're%20not%20majors%2C%20don't%20really%20know%20what%20philosophy%20is%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20%26quot%3BSo%20I%20like%20to%20get%20an%20idea%20of%20what%20their%20expectations%20are%20so%20I%20can%20know%20how%20to%20respond%20to%20them.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20AI-written%20responses%2C%20however%2C%20did%20not%20reflect%20what%20the%20students%2C%20as%20individuals%2C%20were%20expecting%20from%20the%20course%20but%20rather%20a%20regurgitated%20description%20of%20what%20a%20technology%20ethics%20class%20is%2C%20which%20clued%20Fritts%20in%20that%20they%20were%20generated%20by%20ChatGPT%20or%20a%20similar%20chatbot.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhen%20you're%20a%20professor%2C%20and%20you've%20read%20dozens%20and%20dozens%20of%20AI%20essays%2C%20you%20can%20just%20tell%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22e0b552b0-5f55-4bcf-938f-9995306aaa90%5C%22%3EThe%20calculator%20argument%20%E2%80%94%20why%20ChatGPT%20is%20not%20just%20another%20problem-solving%20tool%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20a%20common%20defense%20permeating%20Fritts'%20replies%20likened%20ChatGPT%20for%20writing%20to%20a%20calculator%20for%20math%20problems%2C%20she%20said%20that%20viewing%20LLMs%20as%20just%20another%20problem-solving%20tool%20is%20a%20%26quot%3Bmistaken%26quot%3B%20comparison%2C%20especially%20in%20the%20context%20of%20humanities.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECalculators%20reduce%20the%20time%20needed%20to%20solve%20mechanical%20operations%20that%20students%20are%20already%20taught%20to%20produce%20a%20singular%20correct%20solution.%20But%20Fritts%20said%20that%20the%20aim%20of%20humanities%20education%20is%20not%20to%20create%20a%20product%20but%20to%20%26quot%3Bshape%20people%26quot%3B%20by%20%26quot%3Bgiving%20them%20the%20ability%20to%20think%20about%20things%20that%20they%20wouldn't%20naturally%20be%20prompted%20to%20think%20about.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20goal%20is%20to%20create%20liberated%20minds%20%E2%80%94%20liberated%20people%20%E2%80%94%20and%20offloading%20the%20thinking%20onto%20a%20machine%2C%20by%20definition%2C%20doesn't%20achieve%20that%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2281ba0d50-1afb-4f61-914a-96c48c6a1f92%5C%22%3ELasting%20impacts%20on%20students%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EBeyond%20cheating%20on%20papers%2C%20Fritts%20said%20that%20students%20have%2C%20in%20general%2C%20become%20compromised%20in%20their%20thinking%20ability%20%E2%80%94%20and%20they've%20noticed.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThey're%20like%2C%20'When%20I%20was%20young%2C%20I%20used%20to%20love%20to%20read%2C%20and%20now%20I%20can't.%20I%20can't%20even%20get%20through%20the%20chapter%20of%20a%20book%2C'%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20%26quot%3B'My%20attention%20span%20is%20so%20bad%2C%20and%20I%20know%20it's%20from%20looking%20at%20my%20phone%2C%20always%20having%20YouTube%20or%20TikTok%20on.'%20And%20they're%20sad%20about%20it.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFritts%20said%20that%20technology%20addiction%20has%20affected%20students'%20general%20agency%20when%20interacting%20with%20information.%20She%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fphilpapers.org%2Frec%2FHARSRA-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecited%20a%202015%20paper%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0by%20Professor%20Charles%20Harvey%2C%20chair%20of%20the%20Department%20of%20Philosophy%20and%20Religion%20at%20the%20University%20of%20Central%20Arkansas%2C%20which%20examines%20the%20effects%20that%20interactions%20with%20technology%20could%20have%20had%20on%20human%20agency%20and%20concentration.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHarvey%20wrote%20that%20two%20different%20eye-tracking%20experiments%20indicated%20that%20the%20vast%20majority%20of%20people%20skim%20online%20text%20quickly%2C%20%26quot%3Bskipping%20down%20the%20page%26quot%3B%20rather%20than%20reading%20line%20by%20line.%20Deep%20reading%20of%20paper%20texts%20is%20being%20snipped%20into%20%26quot%3Beven%20smaller%2C%20disconnected%26quot%3B%20thoughts.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20new%20generations%20will%20not%20be%20experiencing%20this%20technology%20for%20the%20first%20time.%20They'll%20have%20grown%20up%20with%20it%2C%26quot%3B%20Fritts%20said.%20%26quot%3BI%20think%20we%20can%20expect%20a%20lot%20of%20changes%20in%20the%20really%20foundational%20aspects%20of%20human%20agency%2C%20and%20I'm%20not%20convinced%20those%20changes%20are%20going%20to%20be%20good.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22c9c300f0-9a0d-4624-aae9-3d4683ca6207%5C%22%3ETeachers%20are%20getting%20tired%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EFritts%20acknowledges%20that%20educators%20have%20some%20obligation%20to%20teach%20students%20how%20to%20use%20AI%20in%20a%20productive%20and%20edifying%20way.%20However%2C%20she%20said%20that%20placing%20the%20burden%20of%20fixing%20the%20cheating%20trend%20on%20scholars%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fai-literacy-ethics-teaching-students-educators-scholars-2024-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eteaching%20AI%20literacy%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20students%20is%20%26quot%3Bnaive%20to%20the%20point%20of%20unbelievability.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BLet's%20not%20deceive%20ourselves%20that%20students%20are%20using%20AI%20because%20they're%20just%20so%20siked%20about%20the%20new%20tech%2C%20and%20they're%20not%20sure%20of%20what%20the%20right%20way%20to%20use%20it%20in%20the%20classroom%2C%26quot%3B%20Fritts%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAnd%20I'm%20not%20trying%20to%20slam%20them%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20added.%20%26quot%3BAll%20of%20us%20are%20inclined%20to%20take%20measures%20to%20make%20things%20easier%20for%20us.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20Fritts%20also%20feels%20just%20as%20%26quot%3Bpessimistic%26quot%3B%20about%20the%20alternative%20solution%20%E2%80%94%20educators%20and%20institutions%20forming%20a%20%26quot%3Bunited%20front%26quot%3B%20in%20keeping%20AI%20out%20of%20the%20classroom.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhich%20isn't%20going%20to%20happen%20because%20so%20many%20educators%20are%20now%20fueled%20by%20sentiments%20from%20university%20administration%2C%26quot%3B%20Fritts%20said.%20%26quot%3BThey're%20being%20encouraged%20to%20incorporate%20this%20into%20the%20curriculum.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20least%2022%20state%20departments%20of%20education%20have%20released%20official%20guidelines%20for%20AI%20use%20in%20schools%2C%20The%20Information%20recently%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Faffiliate.insider.com%3Fh%3Dc5be491442deb8bcd739db23b2e02cdf04b270189b6428bb36c0062f6aa348b6%26postID%3D66db018d92d5b68ffc4b2212%26postSlug%3Dstudents-caught-using-chatgpt-ai-assignment-teachers-debate-2024-9%26site%3Dbi%26u%3Dhttps%253A%252F%252Fwww.theinformation.com%252Farticles%252Fai-isnt-the-enemy-for-some-schools-anymore-flaky-startups-are%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ereported%3C%2Fa%3E.%20A%202024%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.edweek.org%2Ftechnology%2Fwill-ai-use-in-schools-increase-next-year-56-percent-of-educators-say-yes%2F2024%2F02%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esurvey%3C%2Fa%3E%20by%20EdWeek%20Research%20Center%20found%20that%2056%25%20of%20over%20900%20educators%20anticipated%20AI%20use%20to%20rise.%20And%20some%20are%20excited%20for%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECurby%20Alexander%2C%20an%20associate%20education%20professor%20at%20Texas%20Christian%20University%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fai-in-the-classroom-has-some-people-worried-teachers-arent-2024-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Epreviously%20told%3C%2Fa%3E%20BI%20that%20he%20uses%20AI%20to%20help%20brainstorm%20ideas%20and%20develop%20case%20studies%20%26quot%3Bwithout%20taking%20up%20a%20lot%20of%20class%20time.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EASU's%20Anna%20Cunningham%2C%20a%20Dean's%20Fellow%2C%20and%20Joel%20Nishimura%2C%20an%20associate%20professor%20in%20the%20Mathematical%20and%20Natural%20Sciences%20department%2C%20wrote%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.insidehighered.com%2Fopinion%2Fcar