old%20The%20Times%3A%20%26quot%3BThere%20was%20a%20trust%20fund%20set%20up%20at%20the%20time.%20It%20was%20a%20way%20for%20the%20Queen%20Mother%20to%20set%20aside%20money%20for%20her%20great-grandchildren%20when%20they%20were%20older%2C%20and%20a%20way%20of%20passing%20a%20portion%20of%20her%20estate%20down%20in%20a%20tax-efficient%20manner.%20It%20allowed%20some%20of%20her%20estate%20to%20be%20safeguarded%20for%20them.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESources%20suggest%20that%20Harry%20may%20have%20received%20a%20larger%20portion%20of%20the%20inheritance%20than%20his%20older%20brother%20William%2C%2042.%20Insiders%20believe%20this%20is%20because%20the%20Queen%20Mother%20anticipated%20that%20William%2C%20as%20Britain's%20future%20heir%2C%20would%20inherit%20a%20more%20substantial%20fortune%20from%20the%20Duchy%20of%20Cornwall.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWilliam%20became%20Duke%20of%20Cornwall%20when%20he%20was%20named%20Prince%20of%20Wales%20after%20King%20Charles'%20coronation%2C%20inheriting%20an%20estimated%20%2450.2%20million%20from%20the%20estate.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhen%20the%20Queen%20Mother%20passed%20away%20in%202002%20at%20the%20age%20of%20101%2C%20Buckingham%20Palace%20released%20a%20statement%20saying%2C%20%26quot%3BQueen%20Elizabeth%20the%20Queen%20Mother%20has%20bequeathed%20her%20entire%20estate%20(which%20mainly%20comprises%20the%20contents%20of%20her%20houses)%20to%20the%20Queen.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIn%20her%20will%2C%20she%20requested%20that%20the%20Queen%20make%20certain%20bequests%20to%20members%20of%20her%20staff%2C%20and%20these%20bequests%20will%20be%20subject%20to%20inheritance%20tax%20as%20usual.%20The%20Queen%20has%20decided%20that%20the%20most%20important%20of%20Queen%20Elizabeth's%20pictures%20and%20works%20of%20art%20should%20be%20transferred%20to%20the%20Royal%20Collection.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1725778380000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2024-05%2Fr62pavj_prince-harry_625x300_21_May_2