2%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22An%20ex-Mastercard%20executive%20was%20nearly%20scammed%20of%20%24100%2C000.%20Here's%20how%20she%20spotted%20it.%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222189%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22hacking%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66dc89dda0ff598b26659fba%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221369%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EA%20former%20MasterCard%20vice%20president%20of%20product%20shared%20her%20tips%20for%20avoiding%20account%20takeovers%20after%20almost%20falling%20victim%20to%20one.%3Cp%3EPeter%20Dazeley%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EA%20former%20Mastercard%20executive%20almost%20lost%20%24100%2C000%20to%20an%20account%20takeover%20scam.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EScammers%20accessed%20her%20real-estate%20agent's%20email%20and%20impersonated%20a%20title%20company.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EAccount%20takeover%20fraud%20surged%20354%25%20in%202023%2C%20causing%20%2413%20billion%20in%20losses%2C%20researchers%20say.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20can%20happen%20to%20anyone%2C%20it%20seems.%20Even%20those%20who%20work%20in%20the%20finance%20industry.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20former%20Mastercard%20executive%20told%20Business%20Insider%20she%20nearly%20lost%20%24100%2C000%20to%20an%20account%20takeover%20scam%20last%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECatherine%20Woneis%2C%20former%20vice%20president%20of%20CipherTrace%2C%20a%20service%20owned%20by%20MasterCard%20that%20helps%20secure%20crypto%20transactions%2C%20says%20she%20almost%20lost%20most%20of%20her%20life%20savings%20after%20scammers%20accessed%20her%20real-estate%20agent's%20email.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAccount%20takeover%20fraud%20is%20when%20scammers%20gain%20access%20to%20your%20social%20media%2C%20email%2C%20banking%2C%20or%20other%20personal%20accounts.%20Criminals%20usually%20gain%20access%20to%20accounts%20with%20stolen%20credentials%20that%20they%20purchase%20through%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsmall-town-scam-idaho-contractor-payment-social-engineering-2024-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ethe%20dark%20web%20or%20social%20engineering%3C%2Fa%3E%20tactics%20that%20trick%20you%20into%20sharing%20your%20password%2C%20Woneis%20said.%20They%20then%20use%20these%20accounts%20to%20siphon%20away%20your%20hard-earned%20cash.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20number%20of%20known%20account%20takeover%20scams%20grew%20by%20354%25%20year%20over%20year%20in%202023%2C%20resulting%20in%20%2413%20billion%20in%20losses%2C%20according%20to%20AI%20fraud%20detection%20service%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fpages.sift.com%2Frs%2F526-PCC-974%2Fimages%2FSift-2023-Q3-Index-Report_ATO.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ESift%20Science%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20Woneis's%20case%2C%20Scammers%20accessed%20her%20real-estate%20agent's%20email%20using%20%26quot%3Bcredential%20stuffing%2C%26quot%3B%20a%20tactic%20that%20uses%20AI%20bots%20to%20try%20every%20possible%20username%20and%20password%20until%20they%20fall%20on%20the%20correct%20answer.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20fraudsters%20used%20information%20found%20in%20emails%20about%20Woneis's%20transactions%20to%20impersonate%20the%20title%20company%20for%20her%20home.%20The%20fake%20title%20company%20then%20emailed%20Woneis%2C%20asking%20for%20an%20%26quot%3Baccelerated%26quot%3B%20payment.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThis%20is%20a%20very%20typical%20thing%20that%20criminals%20use%20in%20frauds%3A%20They%20try%20to%20implement%20some%20time%20piece%2C%26quot%3B%20Woneis%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWoneis%20said%20she%20checked%20to%20see%20if%20the%20email%20address%20was%20real%20and%20noticed%20it%20was%20appended%20with%20another%20address%2C%20but%20she%20assumed%20it%20was%20part%20of%20the%20company's%20automated%20email%20system.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThey%20sent%20me%20wire%20instructions%20that%20perfectly%20mimicked%20the%20wire%20instructions%20from%20the%20title%20company.%20They%20had%20an%20example%20of%20what%20that%20looked%20like%2C%26quot%3B%20Woneis%20said.%20%26quot%3BIt%20was%20the%20exact%20same%20typography%2C%20the%20exact%20same%20letterhead%2C%20and%20everything%20else.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20only%20differences%20from%20the%20real%20wire%20instructions%20were%20a%20fake%20phone%20number%20and%20email%2C%20along%20with%20incorrect%20bank%20information.%20Woneis%20said%20she%20thankfully%20called%20the%20phone%20number%20she%20originally%20received%20from%20the%20title%20company%2C%20who%20informed%20her%20the%20bank%20account%20information%20was%20incorrect%20on%20the%20form.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BHad%20I%20been%20in%20a%20rush%20and%20called%20the%20phone%20number%20on%20the%20form%2C%20that%20would%20have%20been%20them%2C%20and%20they%20would%20have%20pretended%20to%20be%20the%20real%20estate%20company%20saying%2C%20'Yes%20this%20is%20authentic%2C%20and%20it's%20come%20from%20us%2C'%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20%26quot%3BWe%20could%20have%20potentially%20been%20caught%20in%20wire%20fraud.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWoneis%20said%20she%20would%20have%20lost%20about%20%24100%2C000%20if%20the%20transaction%20went%20through.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWoneis%20now%20works%20for%20a%20cybersecurity%20company%20called%20Fingerprint%2C%20which%20she%20says%20is%20developing%20tools%20to%20combat%20the%20rise%20of%20account%20takeovers.%20Some%20of%20the%20keys%20to%20fighting%20this%20kind%20of%20fraud%20are%20algorithms%20that%20can%20determine%20where%20a%20website%20visitor%20is%20located%20(if%20they're%20using%20a%20VPN)%20and%20systems%20to%20identify%20when%20bots%20are%20trying%20to%20access%20a%20website%20through%20brute%20force%2C%20Woneis%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20you%20think%20any%20of%20your%20accounts%20may%20be%20compromised%2C%20Woneis%20says%20to%20quickly%20change%20all%20of%20your%20usernames%20and%20passwords%2C%20set%20up%20two-factor%20authentication%20for%20any%20sensitive%20accounts%2C%20and%20report%20any%20fraud%20to%20the%20%3Ca%20hr