re%20in%20this%20semi-acceptable%20rhythm%20when%20my%20BFF%20and%20her%207-year-old%20son%20came%20to%20visit%20for%20a%20weekend%2C%20and%20we%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fguides%2Fhome%2Fez-bed-review%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Eset%20up%20an%20air%20mattress%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20in%20Kirby's%20room%20for%20them.%20We%20told%20him%20he%20got%20to%20have%20a%20sleepover%20with%20Mom%20and%20Dad%20and%20Dogga%20(his%20name%20for%20our%2012-pound%20terrier-chihuahua%20mix%2C%20Arthur%2C%20who%20takes%20up%20as%20much%20room%20as%20an%20adult%20human)%2C%20and%20he%20grinned%2C%20clapped%20his%20hands%2C%20and%20hopped%20into%20the%20bed.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThat%20was%20a%20few%20months%20ago%2C%20and%20he's%20never%20left.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%228a1145d5-8af0-4eba-9d23-40a327c022c8%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3EWe%20all%20get%20more%20sleep%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcouple-not-sharing-bedroom-bed-with-partner-pros-2023-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3ESharing%20a%20bed%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%20even%20a%20king-sized%20one%2C%20with%20a%20toddler%20is%20a%20test%20of%20how%20many%20times%20one%20can%20tolerate%20being%20kicked%20in%20the%20face.%20Arthur%2C%20being%20small%2C%20will%20snap%20at%20anyone%20who%20jostles%20him%20under%20the%20covers.%20Kirby%20will%20be%20on%20the%20verge%20of%20sleep%20and%20then%20suddenly%20start%20reciting%20the%20names%20of%20the%20Ninja%20Turtles%20loudly%20and%20with%20great%20vigor.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EBut%20we%20love%20it.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EBedtime%20can%20still%20be%20a%20battle%2C%20but%20it's%20a%20family%20battle.%20We%20watch%20old%2090s%20cartoons%2C%20read%20books%2C%20wrestle%20(he%20loves%20it%20when%20his%20dad%20%26quot%3Bpower%20bombs%26quot%3B%20him%2C%20WWF-modified-for-toddlers%20style)%2C%20sing%20songs%2C%20and%20then%20settle%20in%2C%20all%20four%20of%20us.%20There's%20not%20nearly%20as%20much%20crying.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EOnce%20Kirby%20is%20asleep%2C%20my%20husband%20and%20I%20quietly%20chat%20or%20play%20games%20on%20our%20phones%20or%20read%20by%20booklight.%20Sometimes%2C%20we'll%20slip%20out%20of%20bed%20and%20decamp%20to%20the%20living%20room%20to%20have%20an%20actual%20adult%20evening.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EMore%20often%20than%20not%2C%20though%2C%20we%20go%20to%20sleep%2C%20too.%20I%20stop%20scrolling%20and%20just%20relax%20in%20the%20dark%2C%20my%20sweet%20son%20nestled%20next%20to%20me%2C%20sharing%20my%20pillow%2C%20hand%20outstretched%20to%20hold%20his%20dad's%20on%20the%20other%20side%20of%20the%20bed.%20If%20he%20has%20a%20nightmare%2C%20I%20can%20easily%20calm%20him%20with%20a%20back%20rub.%20And%20I%20don't%20set%20an%20alarm%20anymore%20because%20I%20reliably%20wake%20up%20to%20a%20small%20hand%20patting%20my%20cheek%20while%20he%20shout-whispers%2C%20%26quot%3BMama!%26quot%3B.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThis%20phase%2C%20like%20all%20phases%20of%20too-fleeting%20childhood%2C%20won't%20last%20forever.%20We%20joke%20that%20we%20should%20AirBnb%20Kirby's%20bedroom%20in%20the%20meantime.%20Sometimes%2C%20I%20worry%20that%20we're%20setting%20him%2C%20and%20us%2C%20up%20for%20a%20tougher%20transition%20later%20on%20when%20it's%20time%20for%20him%20to%20sleep%20on%20his%20own.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EBut%20right%20now%2C%20co-sleeping%20with%20our%20toddler%20means%20everyone%20in%20our%20family%20gets%20more%20and%20better%20sleep%2C%20we%20get%20to%20spend%20more%20time%20with%20our%20son%2C%20and%20we'll%20never%20miss%20an%20important%20update%20about%20the%20bee.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fco-sleeping-toddler-family-gets-more-rest-2024-9%